A member of the class of chromenes that is 4H-chromene substituted by amino, cyano, 3-nitrophenyl, and dimethylamino groups at positions 2, 3, 4 and 7, respectively. It exhibits anti-cancer activity.

A 1:1 diastereomeric mixture comprising of R,R,S and S,S,S configuration of platinum(II) complexes with 1,2-bis(aminomethyl)cyclobutane as the carrier ligand and lactate as the leaving group. It is a third-generation platinum anticancer drug approved in China for the treatment of chronic myelogenous leukaemia, inoperable metastatic breast cancer and small cell lung cancer.

A linear hexasaccharide derivative consisting of six 3-O-methyl-alpha-L-rhamnose residues linked sequentially (1->4), with the residue at the reducing end linked glycosidically to the 2-oxygen of L-glyceraldehyde.
A diterpene produced by a diterpene synthase from Allokutzneria albata.
A flavonoid oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group of diosmetin; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A polysaccharide derivative comprising a trisaccharide repeating unit consisting of three alpha-L-rhamnosyl residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->3), with the trisaccharide repeats themselves being linked (1->2); a main component of Pseudomonas aeruginosa A-band polysaccharide (A-PS).
A benzoate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of vanillic acid with the hydroxy group of cyclohexanol.

An iron oxide of nanoparticulate size and poor crystallinity. It is a mineral commonly found in soil and freshwater environments and forms a core structural component in the Fe-buffering ferritin protein. It is also used in the sequestration of heavy element contaminants, and is a precursor of haematite and goethite.

A branched amino decasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 6 by an alpha-L-Fuc-(1->6)-[beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 3 by a beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group.

A branched amino decasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by an alpha-L-Fuc-(1->3)-[beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by a beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group.

A dimethoxyflavone that is the 7,8-dimethyl ether derivative of 7,8-dihydroxyflavone.
A flavonol oxoanion that is the conjugate base of rhamnacene resulting from the deprotonation of the 3-hydroxy group; Major species at pH.7.3.

A branched amino octasaccharide consisting of alpha-D-mannose, beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->6), (1->4) and (1->4), to the alpha-D-mannose residue of which are linked (1->3) and (1->6) two further alpha-D-mannose residues and to the beta-D-mannose residue of which is (1->3)-linked also an alpha-D-mannose residue. The N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end carries also an alpha-L-fucosyl residue via a (1->3) linkage.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprised of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and (at the reducing end) N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked sequentially (1->4), with the reducing-end N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue carrying also an L-fucosyl residue via a (1->3) linkage.

A member of the class benzyl bromides that is benzyl bromide in which the hydrogens at positions 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6 of the phenyl ring are replaced by fluoro groups. It is a versatile derivatization agent in chromatography and mass spectrometry.
A bridged compound and sesquiterpene that is tricyclo[5.4.0.0(2,8)]undecane that is substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6, and 6, and by a methylidene group at position 9.
